definition.value: An aluminium atom having a net electric charge.
A A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine(1+) that is the dilauroyl diester of phosphatidiylcholine.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine(1+) that is the dicaproyl diester of phosphatidiylcholine.
Benzaldehyde substituted at the 4-position by an N,N-dimethylamino group and at C-3 by bromine.
A partially hydrogenated benzophenanthridine carrying an oxo group at C-4, geminal methyl groups at C-2 and a 3-bromo-4-(dimethylamino)phenyl group at C-5.
Any EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the activity of a glutaminase (EC 3.5.1.2) and thus the generation of glutamate from glutamine.
A tertiary amine that is adenine substituted at N-6 by geminal methyl groups.
A phosphorodiamidate ester of N,N-dimethyladenosine in which the NR2 groups on phosphorus are morpholino and N(2)-acetyl-N(5)-L-lysino.
A hydrocarbyladenosine in which adenosine is substituted at N-6 by an isopentenyl group.
A phosphoric ester (phosphate) that has two OH groups replaced by NR2 groups.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both oleoyl.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 are palmitoyl and oleoyl respectively.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which the phosphatidyl acyl group at C-1 is oleoyl.
A monosaccharide sulfate that is D-glucuronic acid esterified at O-3 by sulfuric acid.

An oligosaccharide derivative that is a derivative of an octasaccharide consisting of GlcUAbeta1-3GalNAc(6-O-sulfate) disaccharide units with a Delta(4,5)HexUA(2-O-sulfate)alpha1-3GalNAc(6-O-sulfate) disaccharide unit at the non-reducing end.  It has been isolated from a partial chondroitinase ABC digest of a commercial shark cartilage chondroitin sulfate (CS-C) preparation.

An oligosaccharide derivative that is an octasaccharide derivative consisting of an irregular string of NHAcetyl-substituted and O-sulfated monosaccharide residues with a Delta(4,5)HexUAalpha1-3GalNAc(6-O-sulfate) disaccharide unit at the non-reducing end. It has been isolated from a partial chondroitinase ABC digest of a commercial shark cartilage chondroitin sulfate (CS-C) preparation.

A  phosphatidylglycerol that is an sn-glycerol 3-phosphate backbone ester-bonded to either saturated or unsaturated fatty acids on carbons 1 and 2. A further glycerol substituent is bonded via a phosphomonoester linkage.
The E (anti) isomer of testosterone 3-(O-carboxymethyl)oxime.
The Z (anti) isomer of testosterone 3-(O-carboxymethyl)oxime.

An acetylenic fatty acid that is octanoic acid (caprylic acid) which has been doubly dehydrogenated at positions 2 and 3 to give the corresponding alkynoic acid. It is widely used in perfumes, lipstick, and many common food flavourings.

A 1,3-oxazole having a phenyl substituent at the 2-position and an oxo group at the 5-position. Note that phenyloxazolone is commonly used as a synonym for 4-(ethoxymethylene)-2-phenyloxazol-5-one (PhOx).
The oxime O-ether formed from testosterone and (aminooxy)acetic acid.
A glycosylgalactose derivative consisting of D-galactose having a beta-D-N-acetylgalactosaminyl residue attached at the 3-position.
A glycosylgalactose derivative consisting of D-galactose having a beta-D-N-acetylgalactosaminyl residue attached at the 4-position.
A carbohydrazide obtained by formal condensation between pyridine-4-carboxylic acid and hydrazine.
A D-GalpNAc-(1->3)-D-GalpNAc in which the 2-acetamidogalactosyl group (attached to position 3 of the 2-acetamidogalactose moiety) has alpha- configuration.
The alpha-amino-acid anion resulting from the removal of the proton from the carboxylic acid group of L-thyroxine.
An oxime O-ether that is the histamine derivative of testosterone 3-(O-carboxymethyl)oxime.
The E (anti) isomer of testosterone-3-CMO-Hist.
The Z (syn) isomer of testosterone-3-CMO-Hist.
Transition state of the chorismate mutase catalyzed Claisen rearrangement of chorismate to prephenate.
An oligosaccharide derivative that is a tridecasaccharide derivative, the oligosaccharide portion of the Proteus penneri strain 8 (O67) lipopolysaccharide (LPS) core region.
The anion resulting from the removal of the proton from the carboxylic acid group of 3,3',5-triiodo-L-thyronine.
A pyridinecarboxamide that is the monocarboxylic acid amide derivative of  isonicotinic acid.
An N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminide having a 4-nitrophenyl substituent at the anomeric position.
Any hormone produced by the thyroid gland
The pyranose form of D-galactosamine.
The open-chain form of D-galactosamine.
An N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminide having a methyl substituent at the anomeric position.
A thiolactone arising from formal condensation of the mercapto (sulfanyl) and carboxylic acid groups of L-homocysteine.
A tetrasaccharide composed of three alpha-D-Kdo residues and one acetylated glucosamine residue.  It is a partial structure of chlamydial lipopolysaccharide (LPS).
A cyclic thioester of a mercapto carboxylic acid, containing a 1-thiacycloalkan-2-one structure, or an analogue having unsaturation or heteroatoms replacing one or more carbon atoms of the ring.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine having palmitoyl and 5-oxovaleryl groups at the 1- and 2-positions respectively.
A pyridinemonocarboxylic acid in which the carboxy group is at position 4 of the pyridine ring.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine having palmitoyl and epoxyisoprostanoyl groups at the 1- and 2-positions respectively.
A branched octasaccharide consisting of two repeating tetrasaccharide units; part of the O-specific polysaccharide from S. enteritidis .
An amino trisaccharide consisting of a 3-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronic acid residue, a D-galactosyl residue and an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue (at the reducing end) in a linear sequence.
A sialotetraosylceramide having beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Gc-(2->3)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the sialotetraosyl component.
